{{Quote|Clever, Platt, but there is one man who is just too clever for you!|Andor Javin|<ref name="J8">{{JournalCite|8|Galaxywide NewsNets}}</ref>}}
'''Andor Javin''' was a [[TriNebulon News/Legends|TriNebulon News]] reporter.

==Biography==
Javin operated from the city of [[Camalon]] on [[Trantor]]. He owned a [[Droid/Legends|droid]] named [[V1-CH]], with whom Javin uncovered a possible link between [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Platt Okeefe/Legends|Platt Okeefe]] and rogue newsnet operator [[Cynabar]]. A loyal [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] citizen, Javin reported this to the [[Imperial Office of Criminal Investigations/Legends|Imperial Office of Criminal Investigations]], which showed little sign of following Javin's lead.<ref name="J8" />

At some point in his career, Javin reported on the supposed secret identity of the Imperial agent [[Cronal]], also known as Lord Shadowspawn or Blackhole. He claimed Shadowspawn was an [[Arkanian/Legends|Arkanian]] genetics master named [[Zeta Magnus|K'am'ir Zaarin]]. Zaarin was supposedly in league with a [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] of the then-deceased [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Wilhuff Tarkin]] and had an army of clone warriors.<ref name="DOAE3">{{SW|url=news/the-imperial-warlords-despoilers-of-an-empire-part-3|series=The Imperial Warlords: Despoilers of an Empire|text=Part 3|nolive=1}}</ref>

